17/02/2008
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- Cypriots headed to the polls on Sunday (February 17th) to vote for their new president. Voting in Cyprus is mandatory and any citizen who fails to cast their ballot will be fined 342 euros. Of the nine candidates for the post, the one who wins more than 50% of the total number of valid ballots will become the next president. If none of the candidates wins 50%, a runoff will be held on February 24th between the two candidates with the greatest percentages. The new president is scheduled to be sworn in on February 29th. (CNA, AFP, Focus, Reuters, AP - 17/02/08; Focus, Deutsche Welle, ERT, Famagusta Gazette - 16/02/08)
